    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop the permitted development right to extend upwards",
        "additional_details": "We think these developments could:\r\n- Undermine building safety, creating both risks during building works and long-term risks.\r\n- Devalue flats, leaving leaseholders financially trapped.\r\n- Raise service charges.\r\n- Disrupt daily life, causing noise, dust, and restricted access, ruining residents\u2019 well-being.\r\n- Prioritise profits over communities, neglecting local needs.\r\n \r\nThis petition urges the Government to protect leaseholders, property rights, and communities from exploitation and disruption.",
        "background": "We urge the Government to stop the permitted development right to extend upwards. We think this policy benefits developers & freeholders, harming leaseholders & residents, causing financial, structural, & emotional strain. Meant to ease housing shortages, we think it is now a profit-driven scheme.",
